        <h1>Acquiring Assistive Technology</h1>
        <p>Once we have decided that technology is a need and we&rsquo;ve  explored options that we think might work we need to acquire the assistive  technology.  If the technology is  determined to be a need and written into an IFSP or IEP then the school  district is obligated to purchase the assistive technology.  </p>
        <p>But  what if a parent wants to purchase technology for use at home? Or what if&nbsp;technology was not determined to be a  need but it still might provides some benefit?&nbsp; </p>
<h2>Coming Soon</h2>
        <p>There are a variety of options  available that will be explored in upcoming training materials that will  explore funding options, do-it-yourself assistive technology and assistive  technology reuse. </p>
